1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:28,940
[War of Faith]

3
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:31,920
[Episode 26]

4
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:33,960
Let's have a toast, too.

5
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:34,640
Yes.

6
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,840
We're all contributing to the country.

7
00:01:37,410 --> 00:01:39,850
Stop arguing! Stop arguing!

8
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:41,700
Wei,

9
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,390
do you have any insider information?

10
00:01:44,390 --> 00:01:46,670
Yeah, Wei, tell us.

11
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:47,630
Yes, I do.

12
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,280
But... I can't tell you the details.

13
00:01:51,450 --> 00:01:52,800
Come, tell us.

14
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:53,940
What can't you tell us about?

15
00:01:53,940 --> 00:01:55,270
You don't have to speak.

16
00:01:55,460 --> 00:01:58,620
You just have to nod or shake your head.

17
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,810
Yes, that's right!

18
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,640
Should we follow suit this time?

19
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,260
Yes, yes, tell us.

20
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:13,600
Great!

21
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,070
But, but...

22
00:02:17,940 --> 00:02:18,700
You guys can buy,

23
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:20,180
but you must buy within your means.

24
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:21,440
You can't buy them all,

25
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,220
and especially not if you are going to be borrowing money.

26
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:24,100
Okay.

27
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,680
Wen, do you hear me?

28
00:02:26,829 --> 00:02:27,829
Don't worry, Wei.

29
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:28,990
Yes, don't worry.

30
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,740
Thank you, Wei.

31
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:33,840
We haven't done this in a long time.

32
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,840
We'll do something big this time.

33
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:35,800
Yes.

34
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,760
If we make money this time,

35
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,420
I'll get a new rickshaw first.

36
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:41,210
Wen, you still need to get a new wife.

37
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:43,280
Ms. Zhou.

38
00:02:43,470 --> 00:02:45,880
He doesn't even have an old one. How can he get a new one?

39
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:46,750
When he makes money,

40
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:47,750
you can count on me

41
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,800
to find him a wife.

42
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,220
Please don't, Hao.

43
00:02:50,780 --> 00:02:52,630
Your sister eats 1kg of rice at each meal.

44
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:53,630
I can't afford it.

45
00:02:54,210 --> 00:02:55,880
Are you talking back to me?

46
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:02,400
Doggie.

47
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:04,680
Doggie.

48
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:08,640
I heard you encouraged everyone to buy those bills.

49
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:09,640
You want to buy it too?

50
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:10,480
No, I won't buy it.

51
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:11,680
You'd better not too.

52
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,820
Don't encourage them to buy it either.

53
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:13,920
Otherwise, you'll be blamed.

54
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:15,200
Why would I?

55
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:17,560
My father and I have been traveling for so many years.

56
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,540
Those treasury bills, government bonds, and stocks,

57
00:03:19,540 --> 00:03:21,120
are just different ways to swindle

58
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:21,720
people's money.

59
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,680
It's different this time.

60
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,070
What's so different about this time?

61
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:25,470
It's the same every time.

62
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,560
There's nothing new under the sun.

63
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,320
Don't talk nonsense if you don't understand.

64
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:30,160
This time, we are setting up treasury bills to boost the economy.

65
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,730
It's a major policy initiative of the Party and the State.

66
00:03:31,730 --> 00:03:33,329
Even if you don't support it, don't oppose it,

67
00:03:33,329 --> 00:03:34,590
and don't hold me back.

68
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,329
You don't know what's good for you.

69
00:03:36,329 --> 00:03:38,250
Fine. When you go bankrupt,

70
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:39,920
don't say I didn't remind you.

71
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,450
I will be richer than you even if I go bankrupt.

72
00:03:45,329 --> 00:03:48,410
[The Chartered Stock and Produce Exchange, Shanghai]

73
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:55,480
Boss, this is good. Look, the price has risen!

74
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,400
Young man, look, the price is rising so well.

75
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,320
Do you want to buy some more?

76
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:01,960
No.

77
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,880
It's a pity if you don't buy more.

78
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:10,300
It went up again!

79
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,290
You see how well they're doing?

80
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:50,640
Mr. Liu,

81
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,360
How's the transaction volume today?

82
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,320
Today's transaction volume is huge.

83
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,480
Okay, go get busy.

84
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:55,000
Okay.

85
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,520
Not bad.

86
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,320
The issuance of treasury bills by the Treasury Department

87
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,880
is going better than I expected.

88
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:02,560
It shows that the people

89
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,880
have strong confidence in our government.

90
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:06,000
If we succeed this time,

91
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,270
we won't need to worry about money

92
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:10,130
when we want to build infrastructure in the future.

93
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:15,360
Sir.

94
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,400
Sir, it's Ruolai.

95
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:21,640
Hello, Ruolai.

96
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,160
Sir.

97
00:05:22,370 --> 00:05:24,080
There were some surprises at the exchange today.

98
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,190
Some has been dumping their treasury bills,

99
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:26,410
and the transaction volume is not small.

100
00:05:26,410 --> 00:05:28,000
I am wondering if it could be a bank?

101
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:28,510
That's impossible.

102
00:05:28,510 --> 00:05:29,770
They don't have the guts.

103
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:30,910
The Treasury Department has clearly stated that

104
00:05:30,910 --> 00:05:33,200
banks are not authorized to trade mortgaged treasury bills.

105
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:33,600
Then, I guess

106
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,570
they are not optimistic about the treasury bills.

107
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:37,360
Hence, they are trying to sell them at a higher price, and buy them back at a lower price.

108
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,159
In this way,

109
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,950
they can make profits of more than 10 percent.

110
00:05:39,950 --> 00:05:42,080
Don't tell anyone about this just yet.

111
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:42,800
Yes.

112
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,320
Some people's appetites are so big that

113
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,780
they're not afraid to die.

114
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:55,760
Sir, what happened?

115
00:05:56,770 --> 00:05:58,830
Some people are going to go bankrupt.

116
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,810
Cheers, cheers!

117
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,670
Come on.

118
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,630
Sit down.

119
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,080
Li,

120
00:06:16,110 --> 00:06:17,510
I've dumped almost all of

121
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,360
my treasury bills. What about you?

122
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:21,010
I've sold all of mine too,

123
00:06:21,230 --> 00:06:22,420
I didn't expect

124
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:25,200
these people out there to be so crazy now.

125
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:27,690
They will buy as much as you can throw at them.

126
00:06:27,730 --> 00:06:30,990
This is totally different from what we initially thought.

127
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:33,380
They thought someone is overseeing the game,

128
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:34,990
and they all want to have a piece of the action.

129
00:06:34,990 --> 00:06:38,080
In fact, the real dealer has withdrawn long ago.

130
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:42,280
Once the news is released, it will collapse instantly.

131
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:44,659
At that time, we can then buy it back.

132
00:06:44,659 --> 00:06:47,240
We'll have at least more than 10 percent in profit.

133
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,500
Perhaps, it could even reach 30 percent.

134
00:06:52,260 --> 00:06:53,020
Everyone,

135
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:54,500
listen to me.

136
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:58,670
Don't forget the country when you make money.

137
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:01,480
Donate what you have to.

138
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,760
Otherwise, the people at Nanjing

139
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,140
will be really embarrassed.

140
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:06,360
Of course.

141
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,190
We will donate what we can.

142
00:07:08,230 --> 00:07:10,240
How about I donate 5,000 silver dollars?

143
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,080
5,000?

144
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:12,300
Are you trying to just dismiss the beggars?

145
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,360
I'll donate 8,000.

146
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,720
I'll donate 8,000 too.

147
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,320
I'll donate 10,000 then.

148
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:20,100
I'll donate 15,000.

149
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:30,680
Mr. Yu,

150
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,240
we've bought so many.

151
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,000
When will we dump them away?

152
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,600
It won't end up decaying in your hands, will it?

153
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:40,850
What?

154
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:44,320
You still have no confidence in me, Mr. Kang?

155
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:45,240
Not really.

156
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,150
It's just that...

157
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:49,770
those banks are dumping them.

158
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,159
I feel

159
00:07:51,650 --> 00:07:52,920
pretty insecure about it.

160
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:53,550
Mr. Kang.

161
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,120
Aren't you well-informed?

162
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:59,550
You should go ask around

163
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:04,370
what's Treasury Department's stance regarding this matter.

164
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:11,390
[Astor House Hotel]

165
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:18,050
Mr. Kang.

166
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,090
Mr. Kang.

167
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,150
I got the news.

168
00:08:21,150 --> 00:08:22,950
A few days ago at an in-house cocktail party,

169
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:24,320
Mr. Kong personally revealed that

170
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,560
the Treasury Department will recall the treasury bills in advance.

171
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,290
Are you sure?

172
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,670
The senior officials from the Treasury Department have acquiesced.

173
00:08:29,670 --> 00:08:31,630
This matter is a done deal.

174
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:34,620
It means we can still make money if we buy it now.

175
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:37,110
This news will spread to the people soon.

176
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,090
By then,

177
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:42,179
the retail investors will be crazier than they are now.

178
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:44,560
Nice.

179
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,070
You may leave.

180
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:51,470
Great! Wonderful!

181
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,040
That's wonderful!

182
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,000
Old man, why are you still up?

183
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,040
Ms. Zhou.

184
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,000
How much did you earn?

185
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,280
That's none of your business.

186
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:12,880
Ms. Zhou.

187
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:15,290
You're the best. Tell me, please.

188
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:17,600
Don't worry.

189
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,480
When I make a lot of money,

190
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,240
you...

191
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,160
this old man,

192
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,020
and all of them,

193
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,080
I'll give all of you

194
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:27,610
20% off the rent. Are you happy?

195
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,360
Really?

196
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,660
That would make me very happy.

197
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:32,540
Today,

198
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:33,880
at the stock exchange,

199
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,720
I heard news from Nanjing.

200
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,560
It is said that the Treasury Department

201
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,710
wants to recall the treasury bills early.

202
00:09:40,710 --> 00:09:41,640
What do you mean?

203
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,370
What does that mean?

204
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:46,700
It means the price will rise, and rise drastically.

205
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,080
If this news is true,

206
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,050
it will at least rise to 80.

207
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:52,520
Did you hear that?

208
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,120
What if it's fake news?

209
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,320
How is that possible?

210
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,730
A relative of my cousin's mother-in-law

211
00:09:59,730 --> 00:10:01,400
works at the Treasury Department.

212
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,630
He said that people from the Treasury Department have all bought.

213
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:04,160
Not only that,

214
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,820
they even mortgaged the house.

215
00:10:05,820 --> 00:10:07,760
If staff from the Treasury Department are buying themselves,

216
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:08,890
what does that mean?

217
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,480
In my opinion,

218
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:13,060
it's better to stop when things are good.

219
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,080
Don't be greedy.

220
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,640
Greed won't end well.

221
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,080
Back then,

222
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,610
if it weren't for greed,

223
00:10:19,630 --> 00:10:22,040
I wouldn't have ended up like this.

224
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,200
You were not greedy.

225
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,730
You're not destined to have a life of fortune.

226
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:27,810
I've thought about it.

227
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,680
What if I mortgage the house too,

228
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,610
and keep buying?

229
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,000
That won't do, Ms. Zhou.

230
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,200
Wei have already said

231
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,120
we should only buy within our means.

232
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,360
Wei is just a small employee in the bank.

233
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:40,200
He wouldn't know how much more will the price of the treasury bills rise to.

234
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,450
That's decided by the Treasury Department, isn't it?

235
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:44,250
It's better to ask Ruolai first.

236
00:10:44,290 --> 00:10:45,420
Don't take the risk.

237
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,890
The old man is right.

238
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:47,880
I should ask him.

239
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,800
But he won't tell me even if I asked.

240
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,290
How about I give it a try?

241
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,640
We go back a long way.

242
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:59,370
I think he will tell me the truth.

243
00:10:59,590 --> 00:11:01,390
But even if you ask him directly,

244
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,400
he won't tell you.

245
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,890
If you ask him,

246
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:06,600
"Wei,

247
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,420
when will you dump your treasury bills?"

248
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:10,920
If Wei replies,

249
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,180
"When will I dump my treasury bills?"

250
00:11:13,570 --> 00:11:14,600
It means the price will rise.

251
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,630
That makes sense.

252
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:19,040
This time, Central Bank is in charge of the distribution of the treasury bills.

253
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:22,040
All of them will come across first-hand information.

254
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,480
Any conclusions made

255
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,740
will be very accurate.

256
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:27,690
You won't go wrong listening to Ruolai.

257
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:28,620
I'll go and ask.

258
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,210
Okay. I'll wait for your news.

259
00:11:30,210 --> 00:11:30,650
Okay.

260
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,400
He's here. He's here.

261
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,610
Wei, it's me.

262
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,760
Why are you here?

263
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,460
I'm here to bring you some snacks.

264
00:11:52,460 --> 00:11:53,890
Ms. Zhou made some chicken soup. Try it.

265
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:54,280
Thank you.

266
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,340
Careful, it's hot.

267
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:57,620
Go to bed early.

268
00:11:57,730 --> 00:11:58,400
Wait.

269
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:00,950
I have something to ask you.

270
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:10,360
Come, let's talk outside. Chunmiao's already asleep.

271
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,120
Okay.

272
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:18,880
Sit.

273
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:23,230
Wei,

274
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:26,270
I want to buy some more treasury bills.

275
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,770
Ms. Zhou has earned a lot recently.

276
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:31,590
Do you think it's still profitable to buy now?

277
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:36,120
I know it's hard for you to tell me. But it's okay.

278
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,980
Just tell me if I can should buy it.

279
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,010
I'll figure out how much I will buy.

280
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,540
Looking at the current trend,

