285
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:04,710
80. Are you sure?

286
00:13:13,430 --> 00:13:14,690
But you must remember,

287
00:13:15,020 --> 00:13:16,320
don't ever borrow money.

288
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:16,890
You must...

289
00:13:16,890 --> 00:13:18,150
Buy within your means.

290
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:19,880
Don't worry.

291
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:21,540
You know me.

292
00:13:21,740 --> 00:13:22,740
I'm never greedy.

293
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:25,010
I'll get going then.

294
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:30,710
Are you done?

295
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:31,320
How much?

296
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,160
80.

297
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,000
80.

298
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:34,240
That's great.

299
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:36,880
It means the news from the Treasury Department is true.

300
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:39,890
When it hits 80, be sure to sell it quickly.

301
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,040
Yeah, Wei said that

302
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,730
if this matter goes awry,

303
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,540
many people will go bankrupt.

304
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,060
He's talking about other people, not us.

305
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:50,830
When I become rich,

306
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:53,320
I'll take care of all your lunches.

307
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:54,580
Three dishes and one soup.

308
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:56,910
One meat and two vegetable dishes. Happy?

309
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,880
Yes. Are you for real?

310
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:00,640
When did I ever lie to you?

311
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,080
80.

312
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:18,440
With just this bit of money,

313
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:21,570
I still can't buy a rickshaw even if it rises to 80.

314
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,400
How much do you want?

315
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,600
How much can I borrow?

316
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:42,090
If you have no mortgage,

317
00:15:42,090 --> 00:15:44,000
you can only get a few silver dollars at most.

318
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:44,930
Who says I don't?

319
00:15:45,790 --> 00:15:47,190
Can't I mortgage myself?

320
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:47,920
You?

321
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:54,710
Look at you.

322
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,380
I don't even want it for free.

323
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:56,940
Sir.

324
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,240
I pull a rickshaw.

325
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:01,690
I have a fixed income every month.

326
00:16:01,690 --> 00:16:02,890
So what?

327
00:16:06,260 --> 00:16:07,950
How much can I borrow

328
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,710
against my income for the next ten years?

329
00:16:20,490 --> 00:16:22,350
Ms. Zhou, why don't we dump it now?

330
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:23,440
Dump it now!

331
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:24,200
Dump it?

332
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:26,270
Damn you! What for?

333
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:29,940
It's all about chasing after the market.

334
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:33,300
It's not too late for us to sell when it falls.

335
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,040
But Wei said...

336
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:37,560
Everything is about Wei.

337
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,560
