338
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,690
you shall go to hell.

339
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,680
It's not easy

340
00:16:42,830 --> 00:16:44,730
to come across this kind of market conditions.

341
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:45,800
Let me ask you.

342
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:49,160
Have you made enough to replace your rickshaw?

343
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:49,960
No.

344
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:50,760
That's right.

345
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,640
I've mortgaged my house.

346
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,760
There's nothing I'm afraid of.

347
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:55,160
So what are you afraid of?

348
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,240
When the price rises to 90,

349
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,710
I'll put flushing toilets

350
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:06,000
in all your rooms.

351
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,400
Okay, I'll change my rickshaw when it's 90.

352
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,400
It will have German tires,

353
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,670
Italian bearings,

354
00:17:10,670 --> 00:17:12,640
and French cushions.

355
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:15,280
It's now at 88!

356
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:18,150
You are already making money, and you are still thinking about changing your rickshaw?

357
00:17:18,150 --> 00:17:25,160
90! 90! 90!

358
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,850
Zhang Mingquan, didn't you say that you will

359
00:17:28,850 --> 00:17:31,050
inform us as soon as there is news from Nanjing?

360
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,360
There was nothing I could do. Everybody, calm down.

361
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:34,880
Liar! You are a big liar!

362
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:36,080
It happened so suddenly.

363
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:38,390
I didn’t expect Mr. Kong to be like this either.

364
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:39,490
This is a trap.

365
00:17:40,340 --> 00:17:41,870
Liar!

366
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:44,490
The Treasury Department has been trying to trick us from the beginning.

367
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:46,070
We've already been screwed over.

368
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:47,830
Stop arguing.

369
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,090
It's not necessary.

370
00:17:49,090 --> 00:17:50,480
It's really not necessary.

371
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,540
How could it not be?

372
00:17:51,650 --> 00:17:53,560
Nanjing knew from the outset that

373
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:55,720
we would break the rules to dump our treasury bills.

374
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,320
If we can't close the accounts

375
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:58,480
according to the stipulated amount,

376
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,320
each of us will be charged with

377
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,070
criminal breach of trust.

378
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:03,760
That's punishable by the military law.

379
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,290
They've been waiting for us

380
00:18:05,350 --> 00:18:07,360
from the very beginning.

381
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:07,880
Yes.

382
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,520
Enough.

383
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,880
Stop arguing.

384
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,950
At this point,

385
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:13,850
we can only go back to the stock exchange,

386
00:18:13,850 --> 00:18:15,570
and buy back the treasury bills at the higher prices.

387
00:18:15,570 --> 00:18:17,120
Look at how much the price has gone up to.

388
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,160
How could we buy it back?

389
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,130
How could we?

390
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:21,900
Do you know how much we lost? Have you done the math?

391
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,300
Then we won't buy it back.

392
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,810
We can just face the gallows instead.

393
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:27,420
Let's all get shot, one by one.

394
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:29,320
Do you want your money or your life?

395
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,680
Think about it.

396
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,500
What's the use of arguing?

397
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:36,360
Use your brain and think of a solution instead.

398
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:39,840
Actually,

399
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,760
it's not impossible to buy back

400
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:45,610
the treasury bills at an off-market rate.

401
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,200
How?

402
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:50,000
I do know someone.

403
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,940
He has a lot of treasury bills,

404
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:53,680
and the price is negotiable.

405
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,190
First...

406
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:58,690
Let's start with a ballpark figure first.

407
00:18:58,760 --> 00:18:59,400
90.

408
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,160
What? 90?

409
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,190
Why don't you just go and rob instead?

410
00:19:03,190 --> 00:19:05,200
What's the current market like?

411
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,560
What's the market value?

412
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,160
Yeah.

413
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:08,340
Everyone.

414
00:19:08,370 --> 00:19:09,250
Be quiet.

415
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:10,510
At this rate,

416
00:19:10,540 --> 00:19:12,320
it will rise to 100 sooner or later.

417
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:15,640
And when all of you enter the market, it will rise even more.

418
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,080
90 is already very cheap.

419
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:21,180
And I have sufficient quantity to cover all of you.

420
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:22,900
Use your brains

421
00:19:23,530 --> 00:19:26,500
and cherish this last chance to survive.

422
00:19:32,450 --> 00:19:34,450
Instead of being held accountable,

423
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:38,120
and be punished with your assets confiscated,

424
00:19:38,140 --> 00:19:40,340
why don't you admit defeat now?

425
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,970
At least you can save your life,

426
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:45,650
and have some money for retirement.

427
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:47,880
Everyone,

428
00:19:50,670 --> 00:19:51,700
please cherish

429
00:19:53,230 --> 00:19:55,110
this opportunity

430
00:19:55,290 --> 00:19:57,020
for the sake of your loved ones.

431
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:00,660
Come in.

432
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:02,640
Sir.

433
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:05,490
Something bad is about to happen to the treasury bills, Sir.

434
00:20:05,490 --> 00:20:06,320
Why so?

435
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:08,140
The treasury bills were set up to help with the country's construction.

436
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:09,940
But now, it has gone against the original intention.

437
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:11,280
Those banks dumped their treasury bills illegally,

438
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:12,750
which needs to then be bought back as soon as possible.

439
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:14,210
They're already doing so.

440
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,750
Are they redeeming it at the stock exchange?

441
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:17,800
Whoever they sold it to previously,

442
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,400
they now have to bite the bullet

443
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,830
and buy it back from them.

444
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:23,090
But, the price is up to others to decide.

445
00:20:23,090 --> 00:20:24,360
Within just one transaction,

446
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:25,820
they'll lose everything.

447
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:28,760
Sir, you knew about this long ago, right?

448
00:20:31,710 --> 00:20:32,740
Yes, I knew.

449
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,510
I'm angry too.

450
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:36,450
But for some people, there's nothing I can do.

451
00:20:36,450 --> 00:20:37,770
They are too greedy.

452
00:20:37,930 --> 00:20:39,640
If we don't teach them a lesson,

453
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,900
they will never learn.

454
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,160
If the banks go bankrupt,

455
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,430
what will happen to the smaller investors?

456
00:20:44,430 --> 00:20:45,260
They have real estate.

457
00:20:45,260 --> 00:20:46,250
If we liquidate their real estate,

458
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:47,770
we should be able to fill their accounts.

459
00:20:47,770 --> 00:20:49,900
Then what about the retail investors?

460
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:54,270
Ruolai, this time,

461
00:20:54,290 --> 00:20:56,610
some are opportunists, while others are vermin.

462
00:20:56,610 --> 00:20:58,810
Don't use your kindness on them.

463
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,590
But for some people,

464
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:02,400
they want to contribute

465
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,560
to the construction of Shanghai.

466
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,640
For them,

467
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:07,470
there's no other way.

468
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:09,160
They're on their own.

469
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:24,320
The first one is mine.

470
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:25,920
